body_html: I just figured out that the commit which is required for the squeeze support was actually added after the v1.5 release. Using the latest master commit works just fine. However, it should be considered to backport this feature as the 1.5 docs already list the squeeze operator as supported (more precisely it's listed as removable).

body: I just figured out that the [commit which is required for the squeeze support](ec652809b15b9308d3f9e864cd8d0b97a532b64a) was actually added after the v1.5 release. Using the latest master commit works just fine. However, it should be considered to backport this feature as the [1.5 docs](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/r1.5/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/tf_ops_compatibility.md) already list the squeeze operator as supported (more precisely it's listed as removable).
